'''Nicole Ann Shanahan''' (born September 26, 1985)<ref name = Jacobson>{{cite news|url = https://www.politifact.com/factchecks/2024/mar/26/nicole-shanahan/no-nicole-shanahan-wouldnt-be-the-youngest-vice-pr/|title = No, Nicole Shanahan wouldn't be the youngest vice president in history|last = Jacobson|first = Louis|date = March 26, 2024|accessdate = March 27, 2024|work = [[PolitiFact]]}}</ref> is an American attorney working in [[Silicon Valley]]. She was [[Robert F. Kennedy Jr.]]'s running mate in his [[2024 United States presidential election|2024]] [[Robert F. Kennedy Jr. 2024 presidential campaign|independent presidential campaign]].

Born in California, Shanahan graduated from the [[University of Puget Sound]] and the [[Santa Clara University School of Law]].<ref name="MaslowJuly2023" /> Before law school, she worked as a paralegal and then as a patent specialist at the [[Defensive patent aggregation|defensive patent aggregator]] [[RPX Corporation|RPX Corp.]]<ref name="MaslowJuly2023" /><ref name="Berman" /> She was a fellow at [[Stanford Law School]]'s CodeX, Stanford Center for Legal Informatics.<ref name="Independent" /><ref name="2014ClassNotes" /><ref name="Hamlet2016" />

Shanahan married [[Google]] co-founder [[Sergey Brin]] in 2018; they separated in 2021 and divorced in 2023.<ref name="OBrienFeb12" /><ref name="OBrienMar172024" /><ref>{{cite web |last1=Price |first1=Rob |last2=Langley |first2=Hugh |date=June 17, 2022 |title=Court filings reveal details of Google cofounder Sergey Brin's divorce from his wife, attorney Nicole Shanahan |url=https://www.businessinsider.com/google-cofounder-sergey-brin-nicole-shanahan-divorce-court-filings-2022-6 |work=Business Insider}}</ref> She reportedly has a [[net worth]] over $1 billion, primarily as a result of her marriage to Brin.<ref name=Grind>{{Cite news |last=Grind |first=Kirsten |date=May 22, 2024 |title=A Running Mate's History: $1 Billion, Cocaine, a Fling With Elon Musk |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2024/05/22/technology/nicole-shanahan-rfk-jr-vp.html |access-date=May 24, 2024 |work=The New York Times |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref> In 2019, she established a [[Private foundation (United States)|private foundation]], Bia-Echo, that promotes research to [[Advanced maternal age|lengthen the human reproductive lifespan]].<ref name=Bloomberg2022/><ref name="Folk2024" />

In March 2024, Kennedy named Shanahan as his running mate in his [[Robert F. Kennedy Jr. 2024 presidential campaign|presidential campaign]].<ref name="Astor2024">{{Cite news |last=Astor |first=Margaret |date=March 26, 2024 |title=3 Things to Know About Nicole Shanahan, R.F.K. Jr.'s Running Mate |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2024/03/26/us/politics/nicole-shanahan-rfk-jr-vp-facts.html |work=[[The New York Times]]}}</ref> Shanahan has questioned the [[scientific consensus]] on [[Vaccine efficacy|vaccine safety and efficacy]].<ref name="Astor2024" /><ref name="Li2024" /><ref>{{Cite news |last=Robins-Early |first=Nick |date=March 26, 2024 |title=Nicole Shanahan: from philanthropist lawyer to RFK Jr's running mate |url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2024/mar/26/who-is-nicole-shanahan-robert-kennedy-running-mate |access-date=April 3, 2024 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref>

== Early life ==
Shanahan was born to Shawn and Amy Shanahan (née Wong) in [[Placer County, California]], on September 26, 1985.<ref name = Jacobson/> She grew up in [[Oakland, California]].<ref name=MaslowJuly2023>{{cite news |last=Maslow |first=Nick |date=July 6, 2023 |title=Nicole Shanahan 'Moving On' 1 Year After Alleged Elon Musk Affair, Sergey Brin Split (Exclusive) |url=https://people.com/nicole-shanahan-moving-on-1-year-after-elon-musk-sergey-brin-story-exclusive-7556751|magazine=People}}</ref><ref name=":0">{{Cite news |last=Zadrozny |first=Brandy |author-link=Brandy Zadrozny |date=May 23, 2024 |title=Inside the fringe worldview of RFK Jr.'s VP pick |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2024-election/nicole-shanahan-rfk-jr-vice-pr
